  "response": "Here are some generally considered best economy seat options:\n\n1. Exit Row Seats\n- More legroom\n- Often wider seats\n- Usually near front of economy section\n- Cannot have passengers with physical limitations\n\n2. Bulkhead Seats\n- Located right behind physical barriers\n- No seats immediately in front\n- More legroom\n- Good for families with infants\n\n3. Seats Near Front of Economy\n- Quicker boarding and deplaning\n- Less time waiting\n- Closer to restrooms\n- Less engine noise\n\n4. Window Seats\n- Nice view\n- Something to lean against\n- Control over window shade\n- Fewer disturbances from other passengers\n\n5. Aisle Seats\n- Easy access to move around\n- Can stretch legs into aisle\n- Easier bathroom access\n\nConsiderations:\n- Avoid seats near lavatories\n- Avoid seats near galley\n- Middle seats typically least desirable\n- Some airlines allow free seat selection\n- Consider paying small fee for preferred seats\n- Check seat maps before booking\n\nTips:\n- Use websites like SeatGuru for detailed seat information\n- Check specific aircraft configuration\n- Consider personal preferences and needs",
